Three men have been sentenced to 25 years in prison for defiling a nine-year-old boy. Vitalis Momanyi, Kelvin Musungu and George Omondi were convicted yesterday by Mombasa principal magistrate Edgar Kagoni. They trio committed the offence on April 13 and 15 last year at Kidogo Basi area in Kisauni, Mombasa. Kagoni said the accused need to be removed form society to protect children from their ”heinous” acts. “I’m satisfied that the people who committed the crimes are the ones charged. You intentionally and unlawfully defiled the boy,” Kagoni told the accused. The judge said the jail term will enable the accused to reform